abstract: >-
  biocli is an agent-first command-line interface for querying public
  biological databases. It ships 55 commands across 8 HTTP backends
  (NCBI, UniProt, KEGG, STRING, Ensembl, Enrichr, ProteomeXchange, PRIDE)
  plus the Unimod local PTM dictionary, all behind a strict JSON
  contract (BiocliResult envelope with data, ids, sources, warnings,
  queriedAt, organism, and query fields) so that AI coding agents and
  scripted pipelines can call biocli directly without custom HTTP
  clients. Distinctive features include cross-database aggregation
  workflows (gene-dossier, variant-dossier, enrichment, ptm-datasets),
  a fair benchmark (v2) that reports coverage and quality separately
  against three reference tools (gget, BioMCP, EDirect) while never
  scoring unsupported tasks as zero, and a Reference Dataset pattern
  for local-snapshot data sources such as Unimod. MIT licensed.
